1. cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with network coding rates and achievability of rate vectors. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper studies the impact of edge removal on network communication. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possible category as the paper deals with network structures and their properties. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper discusses encoding functions and their restrictions. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper deals with the complexity of achieving certain rate vectors in networks.
